67329711.ece%5C%22%3Earguing%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20households%20have%20started%20taking%20loans%20for%20real%20estate%20and%20vehicles%20which%20is%20a%20sign%20of%20%E2%80%98confidence%E2%80%99%2C%20not%20%E2%80%98distress%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20how%20serious%20is%20the%20fall%20in%20household%20savings%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20understand%20this%20argument%2C%20note%20that%20the%20economy%E2%80%99s%20financial%20dynamics%20can%20be%20categorised%20into%20three%20main%20sectors%3A%20the%20household%20sector%2C%20the%20government%20sector%2C%20and%20the%20corporate%20business%20sector.%20Each%20of%20these%20sectors%20play%20a%20distinct%20role%20in%20the%20economy%E2%80%99s%20overall%20financial%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20household%20sector%2C%20by%20nature%20of%20saving%20more%20than%20it%20borrows%2C%20accumulates%20surplus%20savings%2C%20which%20can%20then%20be%20channeled%20into%20investments%2C%20lending%2C%20and%20capital%20formation.%20In%20contrast%2C%20the%20government%20and%20corporate%20business%20sectors%20often%20need%20to%20borrow%20to%20finance%20their%20activities%2C%20leading%20to%20deficits%20in%20their%20respective%20financial%20positions.%20%3Cstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20context%2C%20C.%20Rangarajan%2C%20former%20chairman%2C%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Economic%20Advisory%20Council%2C%20and%20former%20RBI%20governor%20and%20D.K.%20Srivastava%2C%20former%20director%20and%20honorary%20professor%2C%20Madras%20School%20of%20Economics%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Fopinion%2Fhow-serious-is-the-fall-in-household-savings%2Farticle67345771.ece%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20reduction%20in%20the%20net%20financial%20assets%20rate%20is%20primarily%20due%20to%20a%20rise%20in%20financial%20liabilities.%20There%20can%20be%20many%20interpretations%20of%20this%20rise.%20An%20optimistic%20interpretation%20of%20this%20rise%20in%20the%20borrowings%20of%20household%20sector%20which%20also%20includes%20non-corporate%20businesses%20is%20that%20this%20sector%20is%20buoyant%20and%20has%20borrowed%20more.%20Nevertheless%2C%20the%20fact%20is%20that%20net%20financial%20savings%20ratio%20of%20the%20sector%20has%20come%20down.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThat%20is%2C%20the%20transferable%20savings%20ratio%20of%20the%20economy%20has%20come%20down%20and%20this%20will%20affect%20the%20borrowing%20programme%20of%20government%20and%20corporate%20sector.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThese%20household%20financial%20assets%20include%20bank%20deposits%2C%20cash%20and%20equity%20investments%2C%20after%20deducting%20debt%20servicing%20and%20consumption.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20government%20relies%20on%20these%20savings%20to%20fund%20its%20capital%20investments%20in%20physical%20assets%20like%20infrastructure%2C%20machinery%2C%20and%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20authors%20explain%20the%20problems%20the%20economy%20will%20face%20due%20to%20low%20household%20savings%2C%20saying%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20rule%20that%20the%20acceptable%20level%20of%20fiscal%20deficit%20of%20the%20Centre%20and%20the%20States%20taken%20together%20can%20be%206%25%20of%20the%20GDP%20is%20based%20on%20the%20assumption%20that%20household%20savings%20will%20be%20around%207%25%20of%20GDP%20and%20the%20net%20inflow%20of%20resources%20from%20abroad%20will%20be%20around%202.5%25%20of%20GDP.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20gives%20a%20borrowing%20space%20of%209.5%25%20of%20GDP.%20This%20borrowing%20space%20could%20be%20shared%20by%20the%20government%20to%20the%20extent%20of%206%25%20of%20GDP%2C%20and%20by%20the%20public%20sector%20enterprises%20to%20the%20extent%20of%201%20to%201.5%25%20of%20GDP.%20The%20remaining%20borrowing%20space%20of%202%20to%202.5%25%20is%20left%20for%20the%20private%20corporate%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20%E2%80%9Cif%20the%20savings%20rate%20of%20the%20household%20sector%20fell%20to%205%25%20of%20GDP%20permanently%2C%20we%20cannot%20have%20the%206%25%20rule.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20authors%20say%20the%20fiscal%20deficit%20will%20have%20to%20be%20lower.%20And%20this%20situation%20will%20put%20the%20budgets%20under%20a%20stress.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThey%20further%20note%20that%20if%20financial%20liabilities%20are%20to%20rise%2C%20gross%20financial%20assets%20of%20household%20sector%20should%20go%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlthough%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20direct%20way%20to%20calculate%20savings%2C%20but%20if%20at%20the%20end%20of%20computations%2C%20the%20estimate%20is%20that%20savings%20are%20down%2C%20it%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20concern%2C%20they%20concluded.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20concern%20was%20also%20echoed%20by%20Saugata%20Bhattacharya%20economist%20at%20Axis%20Bank%20Ltd.%20He%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Feconomy%2Findicators%2Ffalling-household-savings-a-risk-to-indias-world-beating-growth%2Farticleshow%2F103925983.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CHousehold%20financial%20savings%20not%20keeping%20pace%20with%20growth%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20concern.%20Without%20adequate%20domestic%20savings%2C%20funding%20the%20needed%20investment%20will%20require%20large%20foreign%20capital%2C%20which%20is%20often%20volatile.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20achieve%20India%E2%80%99s%20projected%20GDP%20growth%20of%206.1%25%20in%20the%20current%20fiscal%20year%20ending%20March%2C%20the%20government%20needs%20to%20sustain%20investment%20spending%2C%20and%20not%20just%20rely%20on%20private%20consumption%20fueled%20by%20debt%20as%20an%20engine%20of%20growth%2C%20%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20further%20observed%20that%20the%20rise%20in%20financial%20liabilities%20with%20falling%20assets%20levels%20could%20be%20a%20sign%20of%20rising%20inequality.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20household%20sector%20is%20consuming%20by%20borrowing%20more%2C%E2%80%9D%20Rupa%20Rege%20Nitsure%20economist%20with%20L%26amp%3BT%20Finance%20Holdings%20Ltd%20told%20%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20happens%20when%20income%20level%20stays%20stagnant%20but%20inflation%20creeps%20up.%20The%20recovery%20is%20not%20broad-based%20%E2%80%94%20while%20a%20section%20splurges%20on%20luxury%20goods%2C%20others%20are%20borrowing%20to%20stay%20afloat.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695721521000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F14185439%2Fcoins-gebbaa9855_1280.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fa-matter-of-concern-if-household-savings-are-down-and-liabilities-up-former-pmeac-chief%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20order%20to%20achive%20India's%20projected%20GDP%20growth%20of%206.1%25%20in%20the%20current%20fiscal%20year%20ending%20in%20March%2C%20the%20government%20must%20maintain%20its%20investment%20spending%20rather%20than%20depending%20solely%20on%20growth%20driven%20by%20private%20consumption%20fueled%20by%20debt.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fa-matter-of-concern-if-household-savings-are-down-and-liabilities-up-former-pmeac-chief%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Steve%20Coogan%20Boards%20Stanley%20Kubrick%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Dr.%20Strangelove%E2%80%99%20London%20Stage%20Adaptation%20From%20%E2%80%98Veep%E2%80%99%20Creator%20Armando%20Iannucci%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695721170000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FStrangelove-Steve-Coogan.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235735306%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22British%20actor%20and%20comedian%20Steve%20Coogan%20is%20all%20set%20to%20channel%20his%20inner%20Peter%20