any%20details.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Uber%20Eats%20driver%20estimated%20he%20spent%20the%20next%20two%20months%20exchanging%20messages%20with%20dozens%20of%20support%20agents%2C%20but%20none%20could%20restore%20his%20account.%20Most%20reiterated%20that%20he%20had%20been%20deactivated%20for%20%26quot%3Bfraud%26quot%3B%20but%20declined%20to%20provide%20specifics%2C%20according%20to%20the%20screenshots%20he%20shared%20with%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESudden%2C%20unexplained%20deactivations%20have%20become%20commonplace%20for%20workers%20on%20gig%20delivery%20apps%2C%20according%20to%20accounts%20from%20these%20workers.%20In%20many%20cases%2C%20workers'%20options%20for%20getting%20back%20on%20an%20app%20are%20limited%20to%20binding%20arbitration%20or%20appealing%20by%20email%2C%20according%20to%20the%20terms%20they%20agree%20to%20when%20they%20start%20delivering%20orders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsider%20spoke%20with%20eight%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-lyft-drivers-explain-how-they-make-the-most-money-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egig%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20had%20been%20deactivated.%20The%20contractors%20worked%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-eats-ultra-fast-grocery-delivery-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUber%20Eats%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstacart-cuts-minimum-base-pay-for-drivers-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInstacart%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoordash-history-milestones-food-delivery-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDoorDash%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-grubhub-lost-the-delivery-war-to-doordash-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGrubhub%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20all%20described%20being%20deactivated%20suddenly%2C%20including%20after%20minor%20issues%20or%20problems%20beyond%20their%20control%2C%20such%20as%20traffic%20while%20en%20route%20to%20a%20customer%20or%20being%20accidentally%20charged%20for%20an%20extra%20item%20by%20a%20retailer.%20Many%20were%20booted%20without%20explanation%20or%20a%20chance%20to%20deny%20or%20defend%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20workers%20spoke%20on%20condition%20of%20anonymity%2C%20citing%20professional%20repercussions.%20Their%20identities%20are%20known%20to%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRemoving%20a%20driver's%20access%20to%20the%20Uber%20platform%20is%20a%20serious%20decision%2C%20and%20we%20do%20not%20take%20it%20lightly%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20Uber%20spokesperson%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20said%20that%20it%20took%20%26quot%3Bappropriate%20and%20proportionate%20actions%26quot%3B%20against%20those%20who%20violated%20its%20community%20guidelines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20process%20companies%20follow%20for%20deactivations%20is%20often%20unclear%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20they%20sign%20up%20to%20work%20for%20delivery%20apps%2C%20gig%20workers%20agree%20to%20terms%20and%20conditions%20that%20dictate%20missteps%20that%20can%20lead%20to%20deactivation.%20Stealing%20orders%20or%20harassing%20customers%20are%20obvious%20examples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fshoppers.instacart.com%2Fcontracts-next%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInstacart%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20says%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20can%20%26quot%3Bimmediately%20terminate%26quot%3B%20its%20contract%20with%20a%20shopper%20for%20various%20reasons.%20Those%20include%20specific%20offenses%2C%20such%20as%20regularly%20failing%20to%20deliver%20complete%20orders%20to%20customers%2C%20as%20well%20as%20broader%20ones%2C%20such%20as%20%26quot%3Bengage%20in%20or%20encourage%20fraudulent%20conduct%2C%26quot%3B%20its%20website%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20workers%20Insider%20spoke%20with%20said%20they'd%20been%20removed%20from%20apps%20for%20vague%20reasons%20and%20small%20mix-ups%2C%20including%20some%20that%20didn't%20appear%20to%20be%20their%20fault.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%2C%20Steve%20got%20what%20appeared%20to%20be%20a%20form%20letter%20from%20Grubhub%2C%20an%20app%20he'd%20spent%20two%20years%20delivering%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20email%20said%20his%20%26quot%3Bservice%20falls%20below%20the%20industry%20standard%20for%20like%20services%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20region%2C%20in%20%26quot%3Bdirect%20violation%26quot%3B%20of%20his%20agreement%20with%20Grubhub.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20accordance%20with%20Section%2011%20of%20the%20delivery%20partner%20agreement%2C%20you%20will%20no%20longer%20be%20contracted%20to%20perform%20delivery%20services%20with%20Grubhub%20going%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added.%20%26quot%3BThis%20decision%20is%20final%20and%20you%20will%20not%20have%20the%20opportunity%20to%20appeal%20the%20termination.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESteve%2C%20whom%20Insider%20is%20identifying%20by%20first%20name%20only%2C%20made%20his%20living%20delivering%20for%20Grubhub%2C%20as%20well%20as%20for%20Instacart%20and%20DoorDash%2C%20in%20Virginia.%20He%20said%20his%20attempts%20to%20reach%20anyone%20at%20Grubhub%20to%20get%20more%20answers%20were%20unsuccessful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20was%20not%20much%20of%20a%20process%20to%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThey%20didn't%20give%20me%20an%20opportunity%20to%20dispute%20or%20appeal.%20It%20was%20one%20and%20done.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJason%20Picon%20of%20Texas%2C%20another%20gig%20worker%20who%20spoke%20with%20Insider%2C%20received%20the%20same%20deactivation%20note%20in%20February%20after%20driving%20for%20Grubhub%20for%20about%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Insider%20showed%20Grubhub%20the%20form%20letter%20Steve%20and%20Jason%20received%20deactivating%20their%20accounts%2C%20Grubhub%20said%20the%20message%20sent%20to%20the%20drivers%20included%20an%20error.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20dispute%20resolution%20process%20outlined%20in%20our%20delivery%20partner%20agreement%20that's%20available%20to%20all%20drivers%2C%20so%20that%20notice%20was%20incorrect%20and%20we're%20making%20sure%20it's%20corrected%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Grubhub%20spokesperson%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWe%20encourage%20those%20drivers%20to%20reach%20out%20using%20the%20process%20outlined%20in%20their%20contract%20if%20they%20want%20to%20dispute%20their%20removal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225292%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Instacart%20gig%20worker%20with%20shopping%20cart%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6511d5dde2c0220019ef57e4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223528%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20Instacart%20shopper%20leaving%20a%20store.%3Cp%3EMichael%20Loccisano%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'There%20is%20no%20day%20in%20court'%20for%20gig%20workers%20who%20are%20deactivated%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20when%20gig%20workers%20know%20the%20specific%20issue%20that%20caused%20the%20deactivation%2C%20it%20can%20be%20hard%20to%20fight%20the%20delivery%20apps%20to%20be%20reinstated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20Instacart%20shopper%20in%20California%20said%20he%20was%20deactivated%20after%20a%20Total%20Wine%20store%20charged%20him%20more%20for%20a%20bottle%20of%20bourbon%20than%20the%20price%20indicated%20on%20the%20app.%20He%20told%20Insider%20he%20called%20an%20Instacart%20support%20agent%20who%20approved%20the%20purchase%20and%20added%20money%20to%20his%20company-issued%20debit%20card%20for%20that%20purpose.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20deactivated%20later%20that%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstacart%20cited%20the%20Total%20Wine%20transaction%20and%20said%20the%20shopper%20had%20committed%20a%20%26quot%3Bmisappropriation%20of%20funds%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20screenshots%20of%20chats%20that%20the%20shopper%20had%20with%20support%20agents.%20It%20added%20that%20the%20shopper%20had%20made%20%26quot%3Bseveral%20unauthorized%20purchases%26quot%3B%20but%20didn't%20point%20to%20any%20transactions%20other%20than%20the%20Total%20Wine%20purchase.%20The%20company%20didn't%20offer%20additional%20details%2C%20according%20to%20emails%20from%20Instacart%20viewed%20by%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAppeals%20to%20deactivations%20are%20reviewed%20by%20Instacart's%20trust%20and%20safety%20team%2C%20%26quot%3Bwho%20thoroughly%20review%20the%20appeals%20and%20respond%20based%20on%20the%20evidence%20provided%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20Instacart%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20a%20shopper%20can%20verify%20that%20they%20were%20deactivated%20for%20reasons%20outside%20of%20their%20control%2C%20their%20appeal%20will%20be%20approved%20and%20they%20will%20be%20reinstated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERikki%20Nudelman%2C%20a%20DoorDash%20driver%20who%20lives%20in%20Central%20California%2C%20found%20her%20DoorDash%20account%20deactivated%20in%20June%20after%20five%20years%20of%20lucrative%20gig%20work%20in%20an%20affluent%20celebrity%20haven%20between%20Los%20Angeles%20and%20Santa%20Barbara.%20Last%20year%2C%20she%20said%20earned%20%2480%2C000%20delivering%20food%20for%20DoorDash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20whole%20thing%20came%20as%20a%20total%20shock%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI've%20never%20been%20fired.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20calling%20DoorDash%2C%20she%20said%20she%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewas%20told%20she%20was%20deactivated%20because%20of%20late%20deliveries.%20She%20appealed%20the%20decision%20and%20noted%20her%20record.%20Over%20five%20years%20as%20a%20delivery%20driver%20for%20DoorDash%2C%20she%20had%20logged%207%2C000%20deliveries%2C%20had%20high%20customer%20ratings%2C%20and%20was%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhelp.doordash.com%2Fdashers%2Fs%2Farticle%2FTop-Dasher%3Flanguage%3Den_US%23program-work%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETop%20Dasher%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20program%20that%20rewards%20drivers%20with%20perks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENudelman's%20appeal%20was%20denied.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20email%2C%20which%20was%20viewed%20by%20Insider%2C%20said%20the%20company%20was%20%26quot%3Bable%20to%20confirm%20that%20a%20violation%20occurred%20and%20directed%20her%20to%20her%20contract%20with%20DoorDash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPlease%20reference%20the%20%26quot%3BAbusing%20the%20platform%26quot%3B%20section%20within%20the%20Service%20Provider%20Platform%20Access%20Policy%20to%20get%20more%20information.%20If%20you%20wish%20to%20submit%20another%20appeal%2C%20you%20will%20need%20to%20wait%2090%20days%20from%20the%20date%20of%20this%20email%20for%20DoorDash%20to%20review%20your%20next%20appeal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENudelman%20said%20she%20made%20several%20more%20attempts%20to%20appeal%20but%20has%20had%20trouble%20finding%20a%20live%20person%20to%20talk%20to%20and%20faced%20%26quot%3Ban%20endless%20loop%20of%20phone%20calls%20and%20emails%2C%20which%20seem%20either%20to%20be%20ignored%20or%20answered%20by%20robots.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20day%20in%20court%20with%20a%20flesh-and-blood%20human%20being%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20nearly%2060%20years%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%20I%20have%20never%20felt%20so%20devalued%20and%20unsupported%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Insider%20asked%20DoorDash%20for%20comment%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20said%20Nudelman%20%26quot%3Bwas%20repeatedly%20(more%20than%20a%20dozen%20times)%20excessively%20late%20with%20deliveries%2C%20indicating%20abuse%20of%20the%20system%20to%20inflate%20earnings.%26quot%3B%20Nudelman%20denied%20the%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20said%20she%20was%20paid%20by%20the%20hour%2C%20a%20stipulation%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-proposition-22-live-vote-count-results-2020%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EProposition%2022%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20new%20California%20law.%20By%20making%20deliveries%20late%2C%20DoorDash%20said%2C%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bfraudulently%20inflating%20earnings.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20recognize%20the%20serious%20impact%20that%20losing%20access%20to%20that%20platform%20can%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20DoorDash%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20why%20we%20never%20take%20the%20decision%20to%20deactivate%20a%20Dasher%20lightly%2C%20and%20only%20do%20so%20if%20they%20engage%20in%20severe%20conduct%20or%20repeatedly%20violate%20the%20clear%20and%20fair%20policies%20they%20agree%20to%20follow%20during%20the%20onboarding%20process.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BWhile%20no%20process%20will%20ever%20be%20perfect%2C%20we're%20constantly%20engaging%20with%20Dashers%2C%20merchants%20and%20customers%20to%20find%20ways%20to%20improve%20while%20maintaining%20the%20safety%2C%20security%2C%20and%20quality%20that%20all%20members%20of%20the%20DoorDash%20community%20have%20come%20to%20expect.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20DoorDash%20delivery%20driver%20in%20New%20York%20City%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f0a88557bff70019476ee9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20DoorDash%20delivery%20driver%20in%20New%20York%20City%3Cp%3ERibeiro%2FNew%20York%20Daily%20News%2FTribune%20News%20Service%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20new%20law%20could%20help%20delivery%20gig%20workers%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efrom%20being%20automatically%20deactivated%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESergio%20Avedian%2C%20a%20multiapp%20delivery%20driver%20who%20shares%20his%20gig-work%20experiences%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftherideshareguy.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EThe%20Rideshare%20Guy%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20blog%20and%20YouTube%20channel%2C%20said%20the%20unjust%20deactivation%20of%20gig%20drivers%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bhuge%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20gets%20about%2015%20emails%20a%20week%20from%20frustrated%20ride-hailing%20and%20food-delivery%20workers%20who%20say%20they%20have%20been%20deactivated%20and%20have%20been%20ghosted%20by%20the%20delivery%20apps%20when%20they%20try%20to%20defend%20themselves%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAvedian%20said%20he'd%20like%20to%20see%20legislation%20passed%20in%20every%20city%20in%20the%20US%20that%20would%20protect%20drivers%20from%20being%20automatically%20deactivated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegislation%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fastcompany.com%2F90946991%2Fseattle-new-approach-to-gig-economy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ESeattle%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20provides%20a%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20city%20recently%20passed%20a%20measure%20that%20makes%20it%20harder%20for%20apps%20to%20deactivate%20gig%20drivers.%20For%20example%2C%20a%20driver%20refusing%20too%20many%20orders%20is%20not%20an%20acceptable%20reason%20for%20getting%20fired%20under%20the%20new%20law.%20It%20also%20requires%20a%20human%2C%20not%20a%20computer%2C%20to%20review%20any%20appeal%20that%20a%20driver%20makes%20to%20a%20deactivation%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnytime%20a%20driver%20is%20suspended%20or%20deactivated%2C%20an%20appeal%20has%20to%20be%20made%20in%20front%20of%20humans%20as%20opposed%20to%20getting%20fired%20by%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20Avedian%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20whether%20employees%20were%20involved%20in%20deactivations%2C%20Instacart%20and%20Uber%20did%20not%20respond%20directly%20to%20Insider's%20questions%20but%20said%20humans%20were%20involved%20in%20appeals.%20Grubhub%20and%20DoorDash%20told%20Insider%20that%20employees%20determined%20the%20deactivations%20of%20drivers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Uber%20Eats%20rider%20in%20Berlin%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%