C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEconomic%20headwinds%20and%20rising%20house%20prices%20have%20left%20Gen%20Zers%20in%20an%20especially%20difficult%20situation.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEngland%20can't%20imagine%20the%20security%20of%20buying%20a%20house%20or%20growing%20his%20savings.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20working%20since%20I%20was%20barely%20in%20my%20teens%2C%20first%20with%20a%20morning%20paper%20route%20then%20part-time%20in%20retail%20during%20my%20studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20three%20years%20older%20than%20my%20parents%20were%20when%20they%20bought%20their%20first%20house%20in%201995%20at%20the%20age%20of%2021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20make%20on%20average%20%C2%A33%2C000%20a%20month%20as%20a%20freelance%20writer%2C%20roughly%20%C2%A3500%20above%20the%20monthly%20median%20wage%20in%20my%20area%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.payscale.com%2Fresearch%2FUK%2FLocation%3DBath-England%253A-Somerset%2FSalary%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPayScale%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20still%2C%20the%20prospect%20of%20buying%20a%20house%20with%20my%20partner%20feels%20completely%20unachievable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGen%20Z%20people%20living%20in%20Britain%20are%20suffering%20a%20unique%20set%20of%20economic%20challenges%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20the%20first%20in%20my%20family%20to%20go%20to%20university%20and%20consequently%20racked%20up%20almost%20%C2%A365%2C000%2C%20or%20around%20%2480%2C000%2C%20in%20student-loan%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20attend%20university%2C%20I%20took%20out%20both%20tuition%20fees%20and%20maintenance%20loans%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0the%20maintenance%20loan%20paid%20for%20my%20accommodation%20but%20little%20else.%20I%20worked%20part-time%20in%20retail%20and%20as%20a%20freelance%20writer%20during%20my%20studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20graduating%20in%202020%2C%20I%20freelanced%20full%20time%20while%20living%20on%20my%20own.%20England%20was%20in%20and%20out%20of%20lockdown%20and%20I%20managed%20to%20save%20%C2%A35%2C000%20thanks%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20expenses%20aside%20from%20rent%20and%20utilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20my%20master's%20degree%20in%202021%20and%20took%20out%20another%20student%20loan.%20It%20covered%20my%20tuition%20fees%20but%20not%20all%20of%20my%20accommodation%2C%20so%20I%20had%20to%20dip%20into%20the%20money%20I'd%20saved%20the%20previous%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20owe%20nearly%20%2480%2C000%20in%20student%20debt%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%20both%20degrees%2C%20as%20of%20September%2011%2C%20I%20owe%20%C2%A364%2C834.46%20in%20student%20loans%2C%20with%20an%20interest%20rate%20of%207.3%25.%20Before%20June%2C%20the%20interest%20rate%20was%2012%25%2C%20but%20the%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thetimes.co.uk%2Fmoney-mentor%2Farticle%2Fstudent-loan-repayment-2022%2F%23interest-rates%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehas%20reduced%20it%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20due%20to%20the%20cost-of-living%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20British%20students%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20tuition%20fees%20are%20currently%20capped%20at%20%C2%A39%2C250%20a%20year.%20In%202006%2C%20tuition%20at%20a%20UK%20university%20cost%20an%20average%20of%20%C2%A33%2C000%20a%20year%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcommonslibrary.parliament.uk%2Fresearch-briefings%2Fcbp-8151%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EHouse%20of%20Commons%20Library%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%201998%2C%20when%20tuition%20fees%20were%20first%20introduced%2C%20I'd%20have%20been%20paying%20%C2%A31%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20UK's%20cost-of-living%20crisis%20has%20a%20greater%20impact%20on%20younger%20generations%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20UK%20has%20been%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instituteforgovernment.org.uk%2Fexplainer%2Fcost-living-crisis%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520%25E2%2580%2598cost%2520of%2Cterms%2520until%25202027.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecost-of-living%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%202021.%20The%20crisis%20is%20the%20fall%20of%20disposable%20incomes%20in%20the%20UK%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20national%20and%20global%20rise%20in%20inflation%2C%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20Brexit%2C%20and%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20everyone%20will%20be%20affected%20to%20some%20degree%2C%20young%20people%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0who%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20have%20lower%20incomes%20and%20less%20savings%20%E2%80%94%20are%20among%20the%20most%20affected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20freelancer%2C%20the%20money%20I%20make%20each%20month%20can%20fluctuate%2C%20but%20I%20always%20make%20enough%20to%20look%20after%20my%20rent%2C%20bills%2C%20and%20other%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGenerally%2C%20I%20can%20expect%20to%20make%20around%20%C2%A33%2C000%20a%20month%2C%20before%20taxes.%20I%20currently%20pay%20around%20%C2%A31%2C000%2C%20or%20about%20%241%2C250%2C%20in%20rent%20and%20utilities%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20fortunate%20to%20be%20in%20a%20relatively%20decent%20financial%20situation%2C%20but%20I%20still%20find%20it%20impossible%20to%20imagine%20a%20real%20future%20for%20myself%20%E2%80%94%20one%20in%20which%20I%20own%20a%20house%20and%20a%20car%2C%20have%20a%20comfortable%20standard%20of%20living%2C%20and%20the%20thought%20of%20retiring%20before%20the%20age%20of%2075%20isn't%20a%20pipe%20dream.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMy%20parents%20acknowledge%20my%20generation%20is%20worse%20off%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20parents%20had%20me%20in%201999%20they%20were%20able%20to%20raise%20a%20family%20in%20a%20house%20they%20already%20owned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20parents%20said%20they%20never%20had%20it%20easy%2C%20but%20they've%20acknowledged%20they%20wouldn't%20have%20had%20the%20same%20security%20or%20be%20able%20to%20get%20on%20the%20property%20ladder%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey've%20had%20to%20work%20hard%20over%20the%20years%2C%20but%20it%20feels%20as%20though%20their%20hard%20work%20has%20been%20rewarded%20in%20a%20way%20that%20the%20hard%20work%20of%20my%20generation%20isn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20nearly%20half%20of%20young%20people%20in%20the%20UK%20spent%20their%20entire%20monthly%20salary%20on%20living%20costs%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fbusiness%2F2022%2Faug%2F02%2Fwhats-my-future-millennials-and-gen-z-grapple-with-cost-of-living-crisis%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EThe%20Guardian%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%20This%20makes%20saving%20money%20for%20retirement%20or%20for%20a%20home%20seem%20nearly%20impossible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ERising%20house%20prices%20make%20getting%20on%20the%20property%20ladder%20nearly%20impossible%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20June%202023%2C%20the%20average%20house%20price%20in%20Bath%20and%20North%20East%20Somerset%2C%20where%20I%20live%2C%20was%20%C2%A3435%2C313%2C%20up%202.8%25%20from%20last%20year%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flandregistry.data.gov.uk%2Fapp%2Fukhpi%2Fbrowse%3Ffrom%3D2003-01-01%26location%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Flandregistry.data.gov.uk%252Fid%252Fregion%252Fbath-and-north-east-somerset%26to%3D2023-08-01%26lang%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EUK%20House%20Price%20Index%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHomes%20are%20only%20getting%20more%20expensive%20%E2%80%94%20and%20quickly.%20Go%20back%20a%20decade%2C%20to%202013%2C%20and%20the%20average%20house%20price%20in%20this%20area%20was%20%C2%A3250%2C911.%20In%202003%2C%20the%20average%20price%20was%20%C2%A3180%2C278.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20average%20house%20price%20in%201995%2C%20when%20my%20parents%20moved%20in%20together%2C%20was%20around%20%C2%A356%2C000.%20According%20to%20the%20Bank%20of%20England's%20Inflation%20Calculator%2C%20something%20that%20cost%20%C2%A310%20in%201995%20would%20cost%20%C2%A319.48%20in%20July%202023%2C%20an%20increase%20of%2094.8%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20if%20you%20compare%20the%20average%20house%20price%20in%201995%20to%20the%20average%20house%20price%20in%20the%20UK%20in%20June%202023%20%E2%80%94%20%C2%A3287%2C456%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0it's%20increased%20by%20more%20than%20413%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20median%20weekly%20earnings%20are%20roughly%20%C2%A3575%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.payscale.com%2Fresearch%2FUK%2FLocation%3DBath-England%253A-Somerset%2FSalary%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPayScale%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20so%20I'm%20earning%20over%20the%20average%20for%20my%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20girlfriend%20and%20I%20talk%20about%20moving%20in%20together%20in%20a%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20we%20find%20the%20thought%20of%20buying%20a%20property%20almost%20hilarious.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20friends%20and%20I%20are%20resigned%20to%20long-term%20renting%2C%20even%20those%20of%20us%20who%20have%20the%20degrees%20and%20qualifications%20our%20parents%20didn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESaving%20can't%20save%20us%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20chose%20to%20go%20to%20university%20and%20rack%20up%20student%20debt%2C%20and%20I%20could%20stop%20going%20out%20to%20socialize%20to%20save%20more%20money%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0but%20it's%20not%20feasible%20to%20expect%20all%20young%20people%20to%20stop%20living%20their%20lives%20to%20save.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYoung%20people%20are%20struggling%20financially%20not%20because%20they%20get%20a%20latte%20on%20their%20way%20to%20work%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0the%20British%20equivalent%20of%20avocado%20toast%20%E2%80%93%20or%20meet%20their%20friends%20for%20a%20drink%20on%20the%20weekend.%20They're%20struggling%20because%C2%A0it's%20simply%20more%20difficult%20to%20get%20started%20as%20an%20adult%20in%20life%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20more%20difficult%20to%20get%20onto%20the%20property%20ladder%20and%20to%20save%20and%20plan%20for%20the%20future%2C%20whether%20you%20buy%20the%20occasional%20small%20treat%20to%20help%20you%20through%20or%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-gen-z-financially-struggling-living-in-england-uk-2023-9%5C%22%3EBu