%20304%20square%20feet%2C%26quot%3B%20John%20Kernohan%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey'd%20already%20spent%20a%20year%20living%20on%20a%20canal%20boat%20in%20London%2C%20and%20Fin%20didn't%20see%20the%20need%20for%20a%20large%20house.%20They%20decided%20to%20sell%20their%20belongings%20and%20lease%20an%2080-acre%20plot%20in%20a%20Georgia%20forest.%20They%20bought%20a%20lofted%20cabin%20shell%20from%20Derksen%20Portable%20Buildings%20that%20they%20could%20turn%20into%20a%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20a%20year%20to%20turn%20the%20shell%20into%20a%20livable%20home%2C%20which%20they%20named%20the%20Beloved%20Cabin.%20They%20needed%20to%20insulate%20it%20with%20drywall%2C%20install%20a%20wood-burning%20stove%2C%20add%20electric%20and%20plumbing%2C%20build%20a%20bathroom%20and%20kitchen%2C%20and%20create%20custom%20furniture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221125%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22the%20inside%20of%20a%20tiny%20home%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6511cf5b59fd710019f00869%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221390%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20inside%20of%20the%20Beloved%20Cabin.%3Cp%3EUnited%20Tiny%20Homes%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shell%20cost%20%246%2C500.%20%26quot%3BAn%20important%20part%20of%20tiny%20living%20is%20to%20have%20tiny%20expenses%2C%26quot%3B%20John%20said.%20Their%20only%20expenses%20after%20the%20build%20were%20electricity%20and%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%20Fin%20started%20looking%20for%20a%20more%20permanent%20location%20for%20their%20home%20and%20found%20a%20plot%20in%20Lake%20Oconee%20on%20Zillow.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20first%20saw%20the%20site%20that%20was%20filled%20with%20trees%20and%20came%20complete%20with%20a%20natural%20spring%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20we%20were%20home%2C%26quot%3B%20Fin%20Kernohan%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAs%20we%20drove%20away%2C%20we%20immediately%20decided%20to%20make%20an%20offer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBuilding%20their%20sanctuary%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%203-acre%20plot%20with%20its%20own%20creek%20became%20their%20permanent%20home%20in%202015.%20After%20moving%20their%20cabin%20by%20trailer%20to%20its%20new%20site%2C%20they%20put%20down%20roots%20by%20building%20a%20deck%20around%20it%20with%20the%20help%20of%20a%20friend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20time%20they%20chose%20to%20install%20solar%20energy%2C%20a%20rainwater%20collector%2C%20and%20a%20HomeBiogas%20system%20for%20creating%20methane-gas%20cooking%20fuel%2C%20and%20use%20their%20natural%20spring%20for%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20started%20a%20garden%20with%20fruit%20trees%2C%20built%20boxes%20for%20vegetables%2C%20and%20created%20a%20small%20yard%20to%20house%20chickens%20and%20ducks%20for%20fresh%20eggs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20they%20added%20goats%2C%20which%20provided%20fresh%20milk%20and%20natural%20fertilizer%20to%20power%20the%20HomeBiogas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELearning%20how%20to%20live%20small%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Kernohans%20first%20learned%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadu-tiny-homes-could-be-a-big-deal-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etiny-home%20trend%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20someone%20created%20a%20fake%20account%20on%20a%20tiny-house%20listings%20site%20and%20posted%20an%20image%20from%20their%20Facebook%20page.%20While%20the%20fake%20account%20was%20taken%20down%2C%20a%20whole%20new%20world%20opened%20up%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Funitedtinyhouse%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETheir%20Facebook%20page%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20began%20growing%20as%20the%20couple%20answered%20people's%20questions%20about%20their%20lifestyle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeen%20to%20connect%20with%20other%20tiny-house%20owners%2C%20they%20launched%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funitedtinyhouse.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5