e%22%3A%22Celebs%20who%20dated%20their%20famous%20crush%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695712409000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103952734%2Cimgsize-54804.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fenglish%2Fweb-stories%2Ftravis-taylor-to-vicky-katrina-celebs-who-dated-their-famous-crush%2Fphotostory%2F103952734.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F103952734.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EFrom%20Travis%20Kelce%20and%20Taylor%20Swift%20leaving%20the%20Chiefs'%20game%20together%20to%20Vicky%20Kaushal%20manifesting%20his%20romance%20with%20Katrina%20Kaif%2C%20here's%20a%20list%20of%20celebs%20who%20dated%20and%20some%20who%20married%20their%20famous%20crush.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fenglish%2Fweb-stories%2Ftravis-taylor-to-vicky-katrina-celebs-who-dated-their-famous-crush%2Fphotostory%2F103952734.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Disease%20X%20Could%20Bring%20Next%20Pandemic%2C%20Kill%2050%20Million%20People%2C%20Says%20Expert%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20UK%20health%20expert%20has%20said%20that%20Disease%20X%2C%20the%20name%20given%20by%20World%20Health%20Organisation%20(WHO)%2C%20can%20cause%20another%20pandemic%20deadlier%20than%20Covid-19.%20In%20an%20interview%20to%20%3Cem%3EDaily%20Mail%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Kate%20Bingham%2C%20who%20served%20as%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20UK's%20Vaccine%20Taskforce%20from%20May%20to%20December%202020%2C%20said%20the%20new%20virus%20could%20have%20a%20similar%20impact%20to%20the%20devastating%20Spanish%20Flu%20of%201919-1920.%20According%20to%20WHO%2C%20Disease%20X%20could%20be%20a%20new%20agent%20-%20a%20virus%2C%20a%20bacterium%20or%20fungus%20-%20without%20any%20known%20treatments.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EExpressing%20her%20concern%2C%20Ms%20Bingham%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BLet%20me%20put%20it%20this%20way%3A%20the%201918-19%20flu%20pandemic%20killed%20at%20least%2050%20million%20people%20worldwide%2C%20twice%20as%20many%20as%20were%20killed%20in%20World%20War%20I.%20Today%2C%20we%20could%20expect%20a%20similar%20death%20toll%20from%20one%20of%20the%20many%20viruses%20that%20already%20exist.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20world%20has%20to%20tackle%20the%20threat%20from%20Disease%20X%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20world%20will%20have%20to%20prepare%20for%20mass%20vaccination%20drives%20and%20deliver%20the%20doses%20in%20record%20time%26quot%3B%2C%20she%20told%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dailymail.co.uk%2Fdebate%2Farticle-12551251%2Fpandemic-disease-x-covid.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EDaily%20Mail%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20expert%20further%20said%20that%20scientists%20have%20identified%2025%20virus%20families%2C%20but%20there%20could%20be%20more%20than%20one%20million%20undiscovered%20variants%2C%20which%20may%20be%20able%20to%20jump%20from%20one%20species%20to%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20a%20sense%2C%20we%20got%20lucky%20with%20Covid-19%2C%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20caused%2020%20million%20or%20more%20deaths%20across%20the%20world.%20The%20point%20is%20that%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20people%20infected%20with%20the%20virus%20managed%20to%20recover...%20Imagine%20Disease%20X%20is%20as%20infectious%20as%20measles%20with%20the%20fatality%20rate%20of%20Ebola.%20Somewhere%20in%20the%20world%2C%20it's%20replicating%2C%20and%20sooner%20or%20later%2C%20somebody%20will%20start%20feeling%20sick%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ms%20Bingham.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEbola%20had%20a%20fatality%20rate%20of%20around%2067%20per%20cent%2C%20and%20she%20added%20that%20others%20like%20bird%20flu%20and%20MERS%20also%20killed%20a%20large%20number%20of%20people.%20%26quot%3BSo%20we%20certainly%20can't%20bank%20on%20the%20next%20pandemic%20being%20easily%20contained.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMs%20Bingham%20also%20explained%20why%20the%20number%20of%20pandemics%20are%20increasing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20increase%20in%20outbreaks%20is%20the%20price%20we're%20having%20to%20pay%20for%20living%20in%20the%20modern%20world.%20First%2C%20it's%20increasingly%20connected%20through%20globalisation.%20Second%2C%20more%20and%20more%20people%20are%20cramming%20into%20cities%2C%20where%20they%20often%20come%20into%20close%20contact%20with%20others%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ms%20Bingham.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20viruses%20are%20jumping%20from%20one%20species%20to%20another%20because%20of%20deforestation%2C%20modern%20agricultural%20methods%20and%20the%20destruction%20of%20wetlands.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWHO%20first%20mentioned%20about%20Disease%20X%20on%20its%20website%20in%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20that%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Brepresents%20the%20knowledge%20that%20a%20serious%20international%20epidemic%20could%20be%20caused%20by%20a%20pathogen%20currently%20unknown%20to%20cause%20human%20disease%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20WHO%20started%20using%20the%20term%20in%202018.%20And%20a%20year%20later%2C%20Covid-19%20began%20to%20spread%20across%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695712380000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2021-06%2F3edhl1f4_coronavirus-generic_625x300_17_June_21.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdisease-x-could-bring-next-pandemic-kill-50-million-people-says-expert-4424370%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Kate%20Bingham%20further%20said%20that%20scientists%20have%20identified%2025%20virus%20families%2C%20but%20there%20could%20be%20more%20than%20one%20million%20undiscovered%20variants.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdisease-x-could-bring-next-pandemic-kill-50-million-people-says-expe