%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F26114516%2FDA-FP.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDev%20Anand%2C%20who%20was%20the%20first%20hero%20who%20projected%20the%20modernity%20that%20a%20newly%20independent%20nation%20looked%20forward%20to%2C%20would%20have%20been%20100%20today.%20In%20the%201950s%2C%20India%20looked%20to%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20to%20lead%20it%20to%20a%20new%20future.%20Millions%20migrated%20to%20the%20cities%2C%20which%20promised%20jobs%2C%20incomes%20and%20a%20life%20which%20shed%20the%20baggage%20not%20just%20of%20colonialism%2C%20but%20also%20the%20traditions%20and%20customs%20that%20weighed%20down%20the%20past.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnand%E2%80%99s%20two%20compatriots%2C%20Raj%20Kapoor%20and%20Dilip%20Kumar%2C%20had%20their%20own%20personas.%20Kapoor%E2%80%99s%20earliest%20films%2C%20especially%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EShree%20420%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20squarely%20placed%20him%20in%20an%20urban%20context%2C%20but%20his%20city%20was%20a%20place%20where%20the%20poor%20were%20noble%20and%20loving%20and%20the%20rich%20were%20riddled%20with%20corruption%20and%20deceit.%20Dilip%20Kumar%20was%20all%20about%20personal%20tragedy%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20brooding.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20Dev%20Anand%2C%20it%20was%20very%20different.%20He%20was%20a%20city%20man%20and%20even%20if%20his%20place%20in%20those%20cities%20was%20in%20the%20underbelly%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBaazi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETaxi%20Driver%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20or%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EHouse%20no%2044%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%93%20he%20faced%20life%20with%20a%20smile.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20was%20always%20optimistic%20about%20the%20future%2C%20a%20flaneur%20determined%20to%20keep%20moving%20ahead%20%E2%80%93%20it%20reflects%20in%20the%20many%20songs%20on%20him%2C%20which%20showed%20him%2C%20literally%20moving%20%E2%80%93%20by%20car%2C%20by%20jeep%2C%20by%20bus%20or%20simply%2C%20walking%2C%20as%20in%20the%20still%20popular%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EJewel%20Thief%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20song%2C%20%E2%80%98Yeh%20Dil%20Na%20Hota%20Bechara%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20this%20was%20what%20he%20was%20in%20real%20life.%20He%20was%20immensely%20well-mannered%2C%20modern%20and%20liberal%20in%20his%20attitudes%2C%20and%20till%20the%20end%20answered%20his%20phone%20himself%2C%20often%20talking%20to%20his%20fans%20who%20called%20him.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20my%20many%20meetings%20with%20him%2C%20for%20interviews%20for%20my%20book%20on%20his%20production%20company%20Navketan%2C%20I%20rarely%20saw%20him%20pensive%20or%20brooding%20or%20even%20regretful.%20Women%2C%20complete%20strangers%2C%20have%20told%20me%20that%20they%20found%20him%20charming%20%E2%80%93%20this%20when%20he%20was%20in%20his%20early%2080s.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20his%20film%20flopped%2C%20as%20many%20he%20made%20in%20the%20last%20few%20years%20did%2C%20he%20simply%20bounced%20back%20to%20make%20the%20next%20one.%20Pessimism%20or%20feeling%20sorry%20for%20himself%20was%20simply%20not%20part%20of%20his%20life.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Dev%20Anand%20Was%20a%20Stylish%20Icon%20of%20Hindi%20Cinema%20Who%20Reflected%20Indian%20Modernity%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fdev-anand-was-a-stylish-icon-of-hindi-cinema-who-reflected-indian-modernity%5C%22%3EDev%20Anand%20Was%20a%20Stylish%20Icon%20of%20Hindi%20Cinema%20Who%20Reflected%20Indian%20Modernity%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHis%20persona%20was%20that%20of%20a%20westernised%20gent%2C%20on%20screen%20and%20in%20real%20life.%20This%20came%20from%20his%20early%20education%20in%20Government%20College%2C%20Lahore%2C%20where%20he%20studied%20English%2C%20and%20the%20atmosphere%20in%20the%20institution.%20The%20father%20of%20his%20sister-in-law%2C%20Uma%20Anand%2C%20who%20was%20married%20to%20his%20elder%20brother%20Chetan%2C%20was%20the%20rector%20and%20she%20has%20described%20a%20life%20of%20tennis%2C%20picnics%20and%20English%20theatre.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20he%20came%20to%20Bombay%2C%20he%20worked%20in%20the%20censor%20department%20during%20the%20Second%20World%20War%2C%20which%20looked%20at%20letters%20sent%20by%20soldiers%20to%20their%20families.%20His%20social%20life%20consisted%20of%20regular%20evening%20meetings%20with%20other%20young%20hopefuls%20who%20were%20waiting%20for%20their%20big%20break.%20These%20included%20Guru%20Dutt%2C%20Raj%20Khosla%20and%20his%20own%20brother%20Chetan.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20Dev%20Anand%20who%20brought%20noir%20to%20the%20Hindi%20screen.%20His%20many%20roles%20in%20the%201950s%20portrayed%20a%20man%20on%20the%20wrong%20side%20of%20the%20law%2C%20often%20due%20to%20circumstances.%20These%20were%20shot%20in%20the%20dark%2C%20light-and-shadow%20style%20of%20classic%20Hollywood%20noir%20films%2C%20by%20Guru%20Dutt%2C%20Raj%20Khosla%20and%20his%20brother%20Vijay%20Anand.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDuring%20one%20of%20our%20conversations%2C%20he%20told%20me%20that%20along%20with%20Dutt%2C%20he%20saw%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EGilda%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20starring%20Rita%20Hayworth%2C%20and%20this%20inspired%20them%20to%20make%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBaazi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20whose%20script%20was%20written%20by%20Balraj%20Sahni.%20In%20it%2C%20Dev%20Anand%20played%20a%20card%20sharp%20who%20is%20lifted%20from%20poverty%20by%20a%20shadowy%20criminal%20boss%20to%20play%20in%20his%20club.%20It%20is%20a%20film%20that%20holds%20up%20well%20even%20today.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%20he%20was%20making%20films%20till%20the%20last%2C%20they%20were%20flopping%2C%20often%20sinking%20before%20anyone%20even%20took%20notice.%20But%20he%20could%20still%20get%20stars%20after%20just%20a%20call%2C%20such%20was%20his%20goodwill.%20After%20he%20passed%20away%2C%20Aamir%20Khan%2C%20who%20acted%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAwwal%20Number%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(1990)%2C%20a%20film%20revolving%20around%20a%20terrorist%20threat%20at%20a%20cricket%20stadium%2C%20said%20that%20he%20had%20accepted%20the%20film%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmumbaimirror.indiatimes.com%2Fmumbai%2Fother%2Fonly-film-i-signed-without-reading-the-script-was-awwal-number%2Farticleshow%2F16185884.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewithout%20reading%20the%20script%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20a%20tribute%20to%20his%20goodwill%20and%20his%20phenomenal%20legacy%20that%20still%20has%20countless%20fans%20all%20over%20the%20world.%20Many%20of%20his%20films%20still%20have%20a%20fan%20following%20and%20when%20the%20Film%20Heritage%20Foundation%20announced%20that%20it%20was%20showing%20four%20of%20them%20on%20the%20big%20screen%20in%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20country%2C%20they%20were%20booked%20swiftly.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fguru-dutt-baazi-bombay-noir-new-trend%5C%22%3E70%20Years%20Ago%2C%20Guru%20Dutt%20Created%20Bombay%20Noir%20With%20%E2%80%98Baazi%E2%80%99%20and%20Set%20Off%20a%20New%20Trend%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EGuide%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20considered%20one%20of%20the%20best%20Hindi%20films%20ever%20made%2C%20and%20the%20one%20thing%20common%20between%20the%20movies%20he%20made%20during%20his%20successful%20years%20%E2%80%93%20from%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBaazi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%201951%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EJohny%20Mera%20Naam%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi