ssile%20strike.%3Cp%3EEmergency%20Sevastopol%2FTelegram%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EUkraine%20claimed%20it%20killed%20Russia's%20Black%20Sea%20Fleet%20commander%2C%20Viktor%20Solokov%2C%20in%20a%20Friday%20strike.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHis%20death%2C%20which%20is%20unconfirmed%2C%20would%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bremarkable%20achievement%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20ex-NATO%20commander%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20last%20time%20an%20admiral%20was%20killed%20in%20combat%20was%20in%20World%20War%20II%2C%20wrote%20James%20Stavridis.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20killing%20a%20Russian%20admiral%20in%20Crimea%20would%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bremarkable%20achievement%26quot%3B%20by%20Kyiv%2C%20a%20retired%20four-star%20admiral%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERet.%20US%20Navy%20Admiral%20James%20Stavridis%20praised%20Ukraine%20in%20a%20Monday%20post%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20known%20as%20Twitter%2C%20after%20the%20country's%20special%20forces%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.me%2Fukr_sof%2F760%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclaimed%20that%20a%20Friday%20strike%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20a%20Russian%20headquarters%20in%20Sevastopol%20killed%20a%20top%20commander.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20said%20that%2034%20officers%20died%2C%20including%20the%20commander%2C%20and%20that%20105%20other%20people%20were%20wounded%20in%20the%20attack.%20Insider%20was%20unable%20to%20immediately%20and%20independently%20confirm%20these%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reportedly%20deceased%20commander%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20Admiral%20Viktor%20Sokolov%2C%20the%20top%20officer%20of%20Russia's%20Black%20Sea%20Fleet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20confirmed%2C%20Sokolov's%20death%20would%20mean%20an%20admiral%20has%20been%20killed%20in%20combat%20for%20the%20first%20time%20since%20World%20War%20II%2C%20said%20Stavridis%2C%20who%20was%20also%20NATO's%20supreme%20allied%20commander%20for%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20remarkable%20achievement%20by%20Ukraine%20eliminating%20a