0despite%20the%20fact%20that%C2%A0%20there%20has%20been%20a%20virtual%20line-up%20of%20statements%20from%20the%20political%20side%20in%20Canada%20and%20its%20closest%20allies%20in%20the%20west%20and%20a%20raft%20of%20reports%20in%20the%20US%2C%20British%20and%20Canadian%20press%20about%20how%20the%20Canadian%20authorities%20had%20signals%20and%20human%20intelligence%20linking%20Indian%20officials%20to%20the%20murder.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20Canada%2C%20along%20with%20Trudeau%2C%20foreign%20minister%20Melanie%20Joly%20had%20issued%20a%20statement%20soon%20after%20the%20allegations%20went%20public.%20From%20the%20other%20Five%20Eye%20group%20of%20countries%20that%20share%20intelligence%20%E2%80%93%20i.e.%20the%20US%2C%20Britain%2C%20Australia%20and%20New%20Zealand%20%E2%80%93%20there%20was%20a%20slow%20and%20steady%20escalation%20in%20the%20level%20of%20statements%20issued.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22%E2%80%98Prickly%20Nationalism%E2%80%99%3A%20From%20a%20G20%20High%20to%20a%20Post-Canada%20Low%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fglobal-press-views-on-india-canada-row-nijjar-allegations%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Prickly%20Nationalism%E2%80%99%3A%20From%20a%20G20%20High%20to%20a%20Post-Canada%20Low%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20there%20had%20been%20a%20sense%20of%20relief%20in%20India%20over%20what%20was%20seen%20as%20lukewarm%20support%20from%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20allies%2C%20largely%20based%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.li%2FZmRbZ%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EWashington%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%20article%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20article%20had%20claimed%20that%20there%20had%20been%20pushback%20from%20the%20other%20members%20of%20Five%20Eyes%20intelligence%20sharing%20network%2C%20including%20the%20US%2C%20on%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20proposal%20to%20issue%20a%20joint%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20Ottawa%20started%20to%20face%20criticism%20that%20it%20was%20all%20alone%20diplomatically%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EPost%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20was%20strenuously%20denied%20multiple%20times%20by%20the%20US%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fnijjar-killing-us-canada-no-special-exemption%5C%22%3Eincluding%20at%20the%20level%20of%20US%20national%20security%20adviser%20Jake%20Sullivan%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20weekend%20was%20capped%20with%20the%20US%20ambassador%20to%20Canada%20David%20Cohen%20confirming%20that%20intelligence%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fshared-intelligence-of-five-eye-partners-informed-trudeaus-allegations-says-us-envoy-to-canada%5C%22%3EFive%20Eyes%20countries%20had%20actually%20contributed%20to%20the%20body%20of%20information%20which%20led%20Trudeau%20to%20make%20his%20allegation%20against%20India%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20all%20the%20foreign%20ministers%20of%20the%20Five%20Eyes%20countries%2C%20one%20by%20one%2C%20had%20made%20public%20statements.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUS%20secretary%20of%20state%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fblinken-says-india-should-join-canadian-probe-says-us-takes-transnational-repression-seriously%5C%22%3EAntony%20Blinken%3C%2Fa%3E%20went%20to%20the%20extent%20of%20saying%20that%20%E2%80%9Ctransnational%20repression%E2%80%9D%20cannot%20be%20tolerated%20and%20that%20Washington%20was%20not%20just%20consulting%20but%20%E2%80%9Ccollaborating%E2%80%9D%20with%20Canada.%20Australian%20foreign%20minister%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foreignminister.gov.au%2Fminister%2Fpenny-wong%2Ftranscript%2Fpress-conference-new-york-1%5C%22%3EPenny%20Wong%3C%2Fa%3E%20described%20the%20allegations%20as%20%E2%80%9Cconcerning%E2%80%9D%20and%20said%20that%20she%20raised%20the%20issue%20with%20her%20Indian%20counterparts.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUK%20foreign%20secretary%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FJamesCleverly%2Fstatus%2F1704160204739272930%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJames%20Cleverly%3C%2Fa%3E%20posted%20a%20statement%20on%20his%20official%20account%20on%20X%2C%20which%20was%20cautiously%20worded%20but%20called%20the%20allegations%20%E2%80%9Cserious%E2%80%9D.%20Even%20the%20smallest%20Five%20Eyes%20member%2C%20New%20Zealand%2C%20had%20its%20foreign%20minister%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nzherald.co.nz%2Fnz%2Fpolitics%2Felection-2023-new-zealands-serious-concern-at-allegation-indian-government-assassinated-canadian-activist%2FTVGDKN6IZJANNJO26JIEFWPGGU%2F%5C%22%3ENanaia%20Mahuta%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%20say%20that%20if%20the%20reports%20were%20true%2C%20it%20would%20be%20a%20%E2%80%9Cserious%20concern%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20her%20government%20was%20%E2%80%9Cmonitoring%20developments%20closely%20with%20our%20partners%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20no%20public%20condemnation%20of%20India%2C%20but%20that%20was%20not%20surprising%20as%20all%20of%20them%20said%20that%20the%20legal%20process%20had%20to%20take%20its%20course.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20political%20heads%20of%20the%20foreign%20ministries%20of%20the%20Five%20Eyes%20countries%20made%20public%20statements%2C%20there%20has%20been%20no%20such%20declarations%20from%20the%20Indian%20foreign%20minister%20%E2%80%93%20or%20any%20other%20political%20figure%20of%20the%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20bit%20unusual%20as%20Jaishankar%20has%20usually%20robustly%20defended%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20against%20criticism%20from%20foreign%20quarters%20and%20been%20vocal%20whenever%20India%20has%20had%20a%20major%20difference%20with%20the%20West.%20His%20words%20criticising%20the%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.outlookindia.com%2Fnational%2Fexplained-what-jaishankar-said-about-europe-why-germany-chancellor-praises-him-news-263632%5C%22%3EEuropean%20mindset%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20demand%20that%20India%20stop%20buying%20Russian%20oil%20following%20its%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20went%20viral%20and%20turned%20him%20into%20a%20hero%20for%20social%20media%20nationalists.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20also%20Jaishankar%20who%20recently%20led%20the%20charge%20from%20the%20Indian%20government%20against%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fmaking-absurd-claims-does-not-make-others-territory-yours-s-jaishankar-on-china-4339360%5C%22%3EChina%E2%80%99s%20new%20political%20map%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20August%20that%20continued%20to%20show%20Aksai%20Chin%20and%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20as%20Chinese%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20April%202023%2C%20the%20minister%20jumped%20on%20the%20spokespersons%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wionews.com%2Fworld%2Fthey-think-its-god-given-right-jaishankar-slams-west-for-commenting-on-rahul-gandhis-disqualification-578344%5C%22%3EGerman%20foreign%20office%20and%20US%20state%20department%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20taking%20note%20of%20Congress%20leader%20Rahul%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20disqualification%20as%20a%20member%20of%20parliament%20following%20his%20conviction%20in%20a%20defamation%20case.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20West%20has%20a%20bad%20habit%20of%20commenting%20on%20others%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jaishankar%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20somehow%20think%20it%20is%20some%20kind%20of%20god-given%20right.%20They%20will%20have%20to%20learn%20only%20by%20experience%20that%20if%20they%20keep%20doing%20this%2C%20other%20people%20will%20also%20start%20commenting%20and%20they%20will%20not%20like%20it%20when%20it%20happens.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20year%20before%2C%20Jaishankar%20indirectly%20responded%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-us-human-rights-jaishankar%5C%22%3EUS%20secretary%20of%20state%20Blinken%E2%80%99s%20public%20criticism%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20human%20rights%20record%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20noting%20that%20India%20also%20had%20serious%20concerns%20about%20human%20rights%20in%20the%20US.%20Blinken%20had%20told%20reporters%20%E2%80%93%20in%20Jaishankar%E2%80%99s%20presence%20%E2%80%93%20that%20there%20had%20been%C2%A0%E2%80%9Ca%20rise%20in%20human%20rights%20abuses%20in%20India%20by%20some%20officials%E2%80%9D.%20Though%20the%20minister%20kept%20silent%20at%20the%20time%2C%20he%20responded%20indirectly%20one%20day%20later.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20take%20up%20human%20rights%20issues%20when%20they%20arise%20in%20%5Bthe%20US%5D%2C%20especially%20when%20they%20pertain%20to%20our%20community%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20adding%2C%C2%A0%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20in%20fact%2C%20we%20had%20a%20case%20yesterday%E2%80%9D.%20The%20case%20he%20referred%20to%20was%20the%20mugging%20of%20two%20Indians%20in%20Queens%2C%20New%20York%2C%20though%20it%20was%20not%20immediately%20apparent%20why%20Jaishankar%20was%20equating%20street%20crime%20with%20human%20rights%20violations%20by%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAll%20eyes%20on%20UNGA%20session%2C%20DC%20visit%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20last%20week%E2%80%99s%20parliamentary%20special%20session%2C%20the%20foreign%20minister%20left%20for%20New%20York%20for%20the%20UN%20General%20Assembly.%20He%20met%20several%20of%20his%20counterparts%20and%20took%20part%20in%20an%20event%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20UNGA.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThough%20he%20spoke%20of%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fit-is-still-a-world-of-double-standards-eam-jaishankar%2Farticle67340629.ece%5C%22%3Edouble%20standards%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20international%20system%20by%20those%20who%20had%20influence%20and%20dominant%20economies%20and%20a%20section%20of%20the%20media%20sought%20to%20read%20that%20as%20a%20reference%20to%20Canada%20and%20its%20allies%2C%20Jaishankar%E2%80%99s%20focus%20was%20vague.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20name%20of%20the%20market%20a%20lot%20of%20things%20are%20done%2C%20like%20in%20the%20name%20of%20freedom%20a%20lot%20of%20things%20are%20done%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20agricultural%20markets%20for%20wheat%20and%20millet.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20September%2026%2C%20J